# Adapter Env Conventions

## Auto-injected variables

Every adapter sets these before spawning the agent process:

- `AGENT_HOME` — resolved `cwd` of the agent. Used by AGENTS.md and skills for portable path references.
- `PAPERCLIP_AGENT_ID`, `PAPERCLIP_COMPANY_ID`, `PAPERCLIP_API_URL` — from `buildPaperclipEnv()`.
- `PAPERCLIP_RUN_ID` — unique run identifier for audit trail.
- `PAPERCLIP_TASK_ID`, `PAPERCLIP_WAKE_REASON`, `PAPERCLIP_WAKE_COMMENT_ID` — set when context triggers are present.

## Override order

1. `buildPaperclipEnv(agent)` sets base vars
2. `AGENT_HOME = cwd` is set
3. User `env` config from adapter settings is merged last (can override anything)

```typescript
// Pattern in every adapter's execute.ts:
const env: Record<string, string> = { ...buildPaperclipEnv(agent) };
env.PAPERCLIP_RUN_ID = runId;
env.AGENT_HOME = cwd;
// ... wake context vars ...
for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(envConfig)) {
  if (typeof value === "string") env[key] = value; // user overrides last
}
```

## Skills injection

Skills are symlinked into a per-run temp directory and passed via `--add-dir <tmpdir>`. The temp directory is cleaned up in a `finally` block after the run completes.
